  "text": "<html>\r\n    <head>\r\n    <style>\r\n        .unselectable {\r\n          -webkit-user-select: none;\r\n          -webkit-touch-callout: none;\r\n          -moz-user-select: none;\r\n          -ms-user-select: none;\r\n          user-select: none;\r\n        }\r\n      <\/style>\r\n      <\/head>\r\n\r\n<body class=\"unselectable\">\r\n \r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">POLITICAL PARTY<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Types of Party System&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Multi-party or group system:&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A multi-party system is the type in which more than two political parties are allowed to operate and compete for political power in a state. For instance, in the first, second and fourth republic, Nigeria, operated a multi-party system.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">One Party System:&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">This constitutionally allows for existence of only one Political party. This is obtainable mostly in a communist or socialist and fascist\/totalitarian state. A state with a hegemonic political party has one dominant party.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Coalition government arises when no party has a majority in the parliament.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Functions \/ Roles of Political Parties&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<ol style=\"margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt;\" type=\"1\">\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Electoral contest<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Organisation and education of the electorate<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Continuity of policy<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Smooth transfer of power<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Recruitment and training of politicians<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">Opposition government<\/li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin-left:32pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; padding-left:4pt; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt;\">National unity<\/li>\r\n<\/ol>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">NB: National Party of Nigeria (NPN). NPN was the widest spread of, membership in Nigeria during the Second Republic and it was formed by former leaders of Northern People&rsquo;s Congress (NPC).<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Example<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">One of the functions of political parties is to____.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. make laws, B. declare a state of emergency, C. interpret the constitution, D. aggregate interest.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">D (2006\/2007, no 8).<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Example<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The disadvantage of one-party system is that it____.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. makes accountability difficult, B. negates freedom of association, C. emphasize political differences, D. delays decision making<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">B (2008\/2009, no 1)<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">negates freedom of association<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Example<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">One of the distinctive features of one- party system is that____.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. the ruling party is the only legal party, B. communism is banned<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">C. the communist party is the only Legal party, D. elections to the legislature are held at the party&#39;s conferences<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A (2014\/2015, no 1)<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">the ruling party is the only legal party in one-party system.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n \r\n<\/body>\r\n\r\n<\/html>",
  "chapIndex": "POLITICAL PARTY"
}